HEADWORD: Cellulitis
<hw>Cel`lu*li"tis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>cellula</ets> + <ets>-itis</ets>.]</ety> <def>An inflammation of
the cellular or areolar tissue, esp. of that lying immediately beneath
the skin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

